# Paid Leave — Leave Balance Test Scenarios

> Using Paidleave

## Test Scenario 1: Medical Leave — Sufficient Balance

Applicant has taken 5 weeks of medical leave so far this benefit year.
They are requesting two additional periods of 4 and 3 weeks (7 total).

- Max entitlement for medical: 20 weeks
- Balance: 20 − 5 = 15 weeks
- Requested: 4 + 3 = 7 weeks
- Per-type check: 7 ≤ 15 ✓
- Overall cap: 5 + 7 = 12 ≤ 26 ✓ → sufficient

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestMedicalSufficientBalance:
  pl scope Paidleave.LeaveBalance

scope TestMedicalSufficientBalance:
  definition pl.application_leave_type equals MedicalLeave
  definition pl.leave_taken_in_benefit_year equals 5
  definition pl.total_leave_taken_all_types equals 5
  definition pl.leave_periods equals
    [
      Paidleave.LeavePeriod {
        -- length_in_weeks: 4
      };
      Paidleave.LeavePeriod {
        -- length_in_weeks: 3
      }
    ]
  assertion pl.has_sufficient_leave_balance
```

## Test Scenario 2: Bonding Leave — Insufficient Balance

Applicant has taken 8 weeks of bonding leave so far this benefit year.
They are requesting two periods of 3 and 4 weeks (7 total).

- Max entitlement for bonding: 12 weeks
- Balance: 12 − 8 = 4 weeks
- Requested: 3 + 4 = 7 weeks
- Per-type check: 7 > 4 ✗ → insufficient

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestBondingInsufficientBalance:
  pl scope Paidleave.LeaveBalance

scope TestBondingInsufficientBalance:
  definition pl.application_leave_type equals BondingLeave
  definition pl.leave_taken_in_benefit_year equals 8
  definition pl.total_leave_taken_all_types equals 8
  definition pl.leave_periods equals
    [
      Paidleave.LeavePeriod {
        -- length_in_weeks: 3
      };
      Paidleave.LeavePeriod {
        -- length_in_weeks: 4
      }
    ]
  assertion not pl.has_sufficient_leave_balance
```

## Test Scenario 3: Care for Family — Sufficient Balance

Applicant has not taken any care-for-family leave this benefit year.
They are requesting two periods of 6 and 4 weeks (10 total).

- Max entitlement for care for family: 12 weeks
- Balance: 12 − 0 = 12 weeks
- Requested: 6 + 4 = 10 weeks
- Per-type check: 10 ≤ 12 ✓
- Overall cap: 0 + 10 = 10 ≤ 26 ✓ → sufficient

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestCareForFamilySufficientBalance:
  pl scope Paidleave.LeaveBalance

scope TestCareForFamilySufficientBalance:
  definition pl.application_leave_type equals CareForFamily
  definition pl.leave_taken_in_benefit_year equals 0
  definition pl.total_leave_taken_all_types equals 0
  definition pl.leave_periods equals
    [
      Paidleave.LeavePeriod {
        -- length_in_weeks: 6
      };
      Paidleave.LeavePeriod {
        -- length_in_weeks: 4
      }
    ]
  assertion pl.has_sufficient_leave_balance
```

## Test Scenario 4: Multiple Leave Types Taken — Overall Cap Exceeded

Applicant has taken 20 weeks of medical leave and 2 weeks of
care-for-family leave this benefit year (22 weeks total across all
types). They are now requesting 6 more weeks of care-for-family leave.

The per-type balance is sufficient, but the overall 26-week cap across
all leave types is exceeded.

- Max entitlement for care for family: 12 weeks
- Balance: 12 − 2 = 10 weeks
- Requested: 6 weeks
- Per-type check: 6 ≤ 10 ✓
- Overall cap: 22 + 6 = 28 > 26 ✗ → insufficient

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestMultipleTypesOverallCapExceeded:
  pl scope Paidleave.LeaveBalance

scope TestMultipleTypesOverallCapExceeded:
  definition pl.application_leave_type equals CareForFamily
  definition pl.leave_taken_in_benefit_year equals 2
  definition pl.total_leave_taken_all_types equals 22
  definition pl.leave_periods equals
    [
      Paidleave.LeavePeriod {
        -- length_in_weeks: 6
      }
    ]
  assertion not pl.has_sufficient_leave_balance
```
